Basic exercices with image packages¶

Author: Pablo G Tahoces

PIL (Pillow package)

In [1]:
from PIL import Image
In [2]:
fName= "fotoSantiago.png"
In [3]:
img= Image.open(fName)

Show image features

In [4]:
print(img.format)
print(img.mode)
print(img.size)

PNG
RGB
(501, 279)

Displaying the image

In [5]:
img.show()

Show pixel values distribution

In [6]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

h= img.histogram()
plt.plot(h)
Out[6]:
[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x2c52a7d7100>]

Note.- For color images, the histograms for all bands are concatenated.

Changing image size¶

Preserving aspect ratio

In [7]:
img.thumbnail((200, 200))
print(img.size)

plt.imshow(img)

(200, 111)
Out[7]:
<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x2c52a878670>

Without preserving aspect ratio

In [8]:
img_1= img.resize((200, 200))
print(img_1.size)

plt.imshow(img_1)

(200, 200)
Out[8]:
<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x2c52a8e6790>

Simple image manipulation functions¶

Flipping

In [9]:
img_t= img.transpose(Image.FLIP_TOP_BOTTOM)

print(img_t.size)

plt.imshow(img_t)

(200, 111)
Out[9]:
<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x2c52a93dc40>

Rotating

In [10]:

Cropping
